cs.DM, cs.DS, cs.CG, cs.GT, cs.CC

Reasoning: 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics): The paper deals with combinatorial properties of graphs, such as balanced separator number, treewidth, and cycle rank, which are typical topics in discrete mathematics.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper presents new bounds and results on graph parameters, which are relevant to the design and analysis of algorithms on graphs.
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry): The paper discusses the geometric interpretation of some graph parameters, such as separators and treewidth, which are relevant to computational geometry problems, such as mesh generation and surface reconstruction.
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory): The paper studies the complexity of computing and approximating graph parameters, which are relevant to game-theoretic problems, such as network design and routing.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The paper presents lower bounds on the treewidth and cycle rank of graphs with balanced separators, which are relevant to the study of computational complexity of graph algorithms.
